{
  "texts": [
    "The attention weights of the first three layers of both approaches are displayed.",
    "It is observed that the attentions of CP-Prompt keep close to the object for identification alone side with domain shifting, while the Dual-Prompt gradually lose correct focus.",
    "It is evident that for cross-domain learning processes, embedding multi-domain common knowledge before attention better preserves key information in each domain.",
    "Particularly in info-graphs with multiple informational elements, the CP-Prompt approach can more accurately identify primary characteristic information.",
    "ConclusionIn this paper, we propose CP-Prompt, which introduces common and personalized prompts into the cross-modal domain-incremental learning task."
  ]
}